    "legalTitle": "Legal Basis - Article 6.12",
    "legalEffectiveDate": "Effective Date: 7/1/2017",
    "legalHeader": "Early Release and Probation from Imprisonment",
    "p1": "1. If a convict has compensated for the damage caused by the crime, proved to be safe for the public through behavior, has not committed serious violations during the sentence, and has served the following percentage of the imposed sentence, the court may decide on early release and probation considering the prosecutor's proposal:",
    "p1_1": "1.1. not less than half of an imprisonment sentence imposed for a period of up to five years;",
    "p1_2": "1.2. not less than two-thirds of an imprisonment sentence imposed for a period of more than five years up to twelve years;",
    "p1_3": "1.3. not less than three-quarters of an imprisonment sentence imposed for a period of more than twelve years up to twenty years.",
    "p2": "2. When granting early release from imprisonment, a probation period equal to the remaining unserved sentence shall be established.",
    "p3": "3. If a person released early from imprisonment violates the obligations imposed during the probation period, the court, considering the prosecutor's proposal, shall invalidate the probation decision and order the unserved sentence to be served.",
    "p4": "4. If a person released early from imprisonment commits an intentional crime during the probation period, the court shall add the sentence imposed for the newly committed crime to the unserved sentence in accordance with the procedure specified in Article 6.9 of this Law.",
    "p5": "5. If a person released early from imprisonment commits a crime by negligence during the probation period, the court shall decide whether to impose a sentence in accordance with the procedure specified in Article 6.9 of this Law.",
    "p6": "6. A convict who committed a crime specified in paragraph 3 of Article 10.1, paragraph 4 of Article 12.1, provision 4.1 of Article 12.3, paragraphs 2 and 3 of Article 13.1, paragraph 3 of Article 22.1, paragraph 3 of Article 22.4, and paragraph 2 of Article 22.10 of this Law shall not be released early and placed under probation.",
    "note": "Note: Paragraph 6 of this Article shall not apply to a person who was under eighteen years of age at the time of committing the crime."
  },
