    "participants": "Participants",
    "legalTitle": "Legal regulations on the right to meet and communicate",
    "article198_3_title": "Article 198.3 Open Prison - Standard Level",
    "article198_3_text": "A prisoner serving a sentence in the standard level of an open prison may have a long-term meeting once every 30 days, and there is no limit on the number of short-term meetings, sending letters, receiving parcels, and making phone calls.",
    "article198_4_title": "Article 198.4 Open Prison - Special Level",
    "article198_4_text": "A prisoner serving a sentence in the special level of an open prison may have a short-term meeting once every 7 days, a long-term meeting once every 45 days, receive a parcel once every 7 days, and make a phone call once, and there is no limit on the number of letters sent.",
    "article199_4_title": "Article 199.4 Closed Prison - Standard Level",
    "article199_4_text": "A prisoner serving a sentence in the standard level of a closed prison may have a short-term meeting once every 60 days, a long-term meeting once every 90 days, receive a parcel once every 30 days, and make a phone call once."
  },
